# A vendored Git source pinned to a moving branch. setupDev creates a local repo (offline, no network) where branch
# `dev` returns 1; `run 1` links and asserts it. moveDev advances `dev` to return 2; after `reload` (which clears
# sbt's in-session config memoisation - the action cache persists on disk, exactly as vendored/cache relies on) `run 2`
# must reflect the move. The plugin resolves the branch to its current commit and keys the vendored cache on that
# commit, so the moved branch is a cache miss and rebuilds. A stale-frozen (uri@ref) key would reuse the first archive
# and `run 2` would fail asserting 1 != 2.
> setupDev
> run 1
> moveDev
> reload
> run 2
